						               													<description>A compilation of 3 games in a wooden box, cover and bottom showing 2 of 3 boards. In addition, there is a board for Nine Men's Morris.&amp;#10;Components: 2 x 48 wooden blocks&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Stratira: Very close to  Score Four. Scoring is different as you may continue after having 4 in a row to get a better score. Details of the rules in BGG Weblink.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;K&amp;ouml;nigshalma: Very close to Halma. Played on a chess board (inside and outside of the box). Necessary components: King, 2 rooks and 7 pawns in 2 colors of a chess game (not provided). 2 x 6 standard pawns (of draughts e.g.) for the 4 player game needed. The blocks of the game could do well. (Not applicable for 3 players.)&amp;#10;The rules for 2 players are a mix of Halma and Salta as the pawns are to be moved to their mirror space at the other end of the board. The rules say you cannot change the color of the space because otherwise it would be impossible to enter the finish spaces (which is hard to believe).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Turm: Very close to Checkers. Played on a chess board (inside and outside of the box). Start: First row is empty, the next 2 rows have all spaces occupied. Moving is forwards and sidewards only. At the finish line, the pawn will be upgraded to a &amp;quot;Turm&amp;quot;, like a &amp;quot;King&amp;quot; in Checkers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Estimated year: 1990&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
